abstract: New York will give Amazon more than $1.2 billion in incentives to establish a hub in the city, and not everyone thinks it’s worth it.

abstract: The cabinet’s support relieves some of the pressure on Prime Minister Theresa May, but there are several steps before the agreement could take effect.
snippet: The cabinet’s support relieves some of the pressure on Prime Minister Theresa May, but there are several steps before the agreement could take effect.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Theresa May’s cabinet approved a draft agreement on Britain’s withdrawal from the European Union during an emergency meeting on Wednesday, a crucial and perilous step, as the time left to strike a final deal runs short.

headline_main: Amazon Is Getting at Least $1.7 Billion to Come to Queens. Now Comes the Fight Over Whether It’s Worth It.
headline_print_headline: Cost of Queens Prize: $1.7 Billion and Up

abstract: The company has gobbled up leases for so much space in so many cities that its landlords might not be able to afford for it to go under.

abstract: Amazon promises tens of thousands of new jobs, but should we expect more than that?
snippet: Amazon promises tens of thousands of new jobs, but should we expect more than that?
lead_paragraph: The innovation myth used to involve the back of a suburban garage or an office park in Silicon Valley. The tech industry was incubated not on the mean streets of the big city, but in sleepy hamlets like Murray Hill, N.J., and Mountain View, Calif.

abstract: Applications Open for the 2019 New York Portfolio Review
snippet: Applications Open for the 2019 New York Portfolio Review
lead_paragraph: It takes time, passion and obsession to make great work. But you also need the opportunity to have your work seen in the first place. And since we at Lens believe only the quality of work should matter — not your connections or bank account — we are again bringing together 160 talented photographers with 75 top photo editors, publishers, curators, gallery owners and video producers, for the 7th annual New York Portfolio Review on March 30 and 31 in New York City.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Why Corporate America Is Content With the Midterms

abstract: Despite warnings from within the G.O.P., Republicans lost their unity and grip on messaging, allowing the Democrats to gain a majority of congressional seats.
snippet: Despite warnings from within the G.O.P., Republicans lost their unity and grip on messaging, allowing the Democrats to gain a majority of congressional seats.
lead_paragraph: The message from Representative Kevin McCarthy, the House majority leader, was urgent and unsparing. In a meeting with Republican lawmakers before they left Washington for the August congressional recess, Mr. McCarthy warned that time was running short: Unless they intensified their campaign efforts and forcefully delivered a coherent message, he said, Republicans would suffer grievous losses in November.
